Others: Anthony Davis admitted that he is being hampered by a foot injury after scoring 31 points, nine rebounds, and four blocks in a win over the Philadelphia 76ers.
Others (Continued): Davis has played through ailments so far this season, but sat out a game due to a heel contusion. Despite playing at less than 100 percent, Davis is an early-season MVP candidate with league-leading 32.4 points per game.
